# C++ Conventions

## File pairing

| Header | Source |
|--------|--------|
| `include/Board.h` | `src/Board.cpp` |
| `include/Game.h` | `src/Game.cpp` |

New classes: add both files and register in `build.bat` + `CMakeLists.txt`.

## Includes

```cpp
// Headers: own guard first, then STL
#include "Board.h"
#include <vector>
#include <string>

// Sources: own header first, then STL, then iostream if needed
#include "Game.h"
#include <iostream>
```

## Patterns in this codebase

```cpp
// ✅ Bounds before access
if (!board.isWithinBounds(pos)) return;

// ✅ Parse with trim + istringstream (see main.cpp, Board.cpp)
std::string cleanLine = trim(lines[index]);
std::istringstream iss(cleanLine);

// ✅ Errors to stdout, return false from setup parsers
std::cout << "ERROR UNKNOWN_TOKEN\n";
return false;
```

## Avoid

- Raw pointers for ownership; use `std::vector`, `std::string`
- Duplicating `trim()` — exists in both `main.cpp` and `Board.cpp` (extract only if asked)
- Changing public command protocol without explicit request
